17 deannexed in one action and only upon the adoption of a resolution by the governing
18 authority of the county in which such property is located consenting to such deannexation.
19 If the governing authority of the county consents to the deannexation and the deannexation
20 conforms with the requirements of this article, the governing authority of the municipal
21 corporation shall approve such deannexation unless it finds that the deannexation would
22 be detrimental to the health, safety, and welfare of the residents and property owners of the
23 area to be deannexed or to the area remaining within the municipality. If the county is the
24 owner of all parcels proposed for deannexation and the governing authority of the county
25 consents, the governing authority of the municipal corporation shall approve such
26 deannexation within 90 days of the date of the filing of a deannexation application unless
27 it finds that the deannexation would be detrimental to the health, safety, and welfare of the
28 residents and property owners of the area to be deannexed or to the area remaining within
29 the municipality."
30 SECTION 2.
31 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
32 without such approval.
33 SECTION 3.
34 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
